The '''Metasploit Project''' is an [[open-source]] [[computer security]] project which provides information about [[vulnerability (computer science)|security vulnerabilities]] and aids in penetration testing and [[Intrusion-detection system|IDS signature]] development.
Its most well-known sub-project is the '''Metasploit Framework''', a tool for developing and executing [[Exploit (computer security)|exploit]] code against a remote target machine. Other important sub-projects include the Opcode Database, [[shellcode]] archive, and security research.
